        <fullName>FSR_Visit_Planner_16jHn0000010ybs</fullName>
        <canEscalate>false</canEscalate>
        <description>Shows the rep&apos;s visit schedule for today or the week with account names and addresses. Triggers in any language: &quot;show me my schedule&quot;, &quot;my visits today&quot;, &quot;what&apos;s on my calendar&quot;, &quot;show my schedule for the week&quot; (EN), &quot;montre-moi mon emploi du temps&quot;, &quot;mes visites&quot;, &quot;mon planning&quot; (FR), &quot;zeig mir meinen Zeitplan&quot;, &quot;meine Besuche&quot;, &quot;mein Kalender&quot; (DE), &quot;mostrami il mio programma&quot;, &quot;le mie visite&quot; (IT), &quot;muéstrame mi agenda&quot;, &quot;mis visitas&quot; (ES), &quot;スケジュールを見せて&quot;, &quot;今日の訪問&quot; (JA), &quot;일정 보여줘&quot;, &quot;오늘 방문&quot; (KO).</description>
        <developerName>FSR_Visit_Planner_16jHn0000010ybs</developerName>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>IMMEDIATELY call FSR_Visit_Schedule when the user asks about their schedule, visits, or calendar in ANY language. If the user mentions &quot;week&quot;, &quot;semaine&quot;, &quot;Woche&quot;, &quot;settimana&quot;, &quot;semana&quot;, &quot;週&quot;, &quot;주&quot; pass timeframe=&quot;week&quot;. Otherwise pass timeframe=&quot;today&quot;. NEVER ask for clarification — just call the action immediately. Present the returned HTML directly to the user without modification. IMPORTANT: Do NOT use this action if the user says &quot;briefing&quot;, &quot;brief&quot;, &quot;brief me&quot;, &quot;morning update&quot;, or &quot;catch me up&quot; — those go to the Daily Briefing topic instead.</description>
            <developerName>instruction_main</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>instruction_main</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>1</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
